From: Jonathan Cameron <Jonathan.Cameron@huawei.com>
Date: Sun, 9 Mar 2025 17:06:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] iio: light: gp2ap020a00f: Switch to sparse friendly
 iio_device_claim/release_direct()
Git-commit: 403443117b0234b8dfe834a077fbac693e6c9d7e
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: jsc#PED-15409

These new functions allow sparse to find failures to release
direct mode reducing chances of bugs over the claim_direct_mode()
functions that are deprecated.

Reviewed-by: David Lechner <dlechner@baylibre.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250309170633.1347476-3-jic23@kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Jonathan Cameron <Jonathan.Cameron@huawei.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.com>
---
 drivers/iio/light/gp2ap020a00f.c | 7 +++----
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/iio/light/gp2ap020a00f.c b/drivers/iio/light/gp2ap020a00f.c
index 1a352c88598e..c7df4b258e2c 100644
--- a/drivers/iio/light/gp2ap020a00f.c
+++ b/drivers/iio/light/gp2ap020a00f.c
@@ -1283,12 +1283,11 @@ static int gp2ap020a00f_read_raw(struct iio_dev *indio_dev,
 	int err = -EINVAL;
 
 	if (mask == IIO_CHAN_INFO_RAW) {
-		err = iio_device_claim_direct_mode(indio_dev);
-		if (err)
-			return err;
+		if (!iio_device_claim_direct(indio_dev))
+			return -EBUSY;
 
 		err = gp2ap020a00f_read_channel(data, chan, val);
-		iio_device_release_direct_mode(indio_dev);
+		iio_device_release_direct(indio_dev);
 	}
 	return err < 0 ? err : IIO_VAL_INT;
 }
-- 
2.43.0

